sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as "AI Platform"
    participant Bridge as "POST /mcp endpoint"
    participant Transport as "StreamableHTTPServerTransport"
    participant Sessions as "sessions Map"
    participant EventStore as "InMemoryEventStore"
    participant MCPServer as "MCP Server"
    
    Note over Client,MCPServer: Initialization
    Client->>Bridge: POST /mcp (no session ID)<br/>isInitializeRequest() == true
    Bridge->>Transport: new StreamableHTTPServerTransport({<br/>sessionIdGenerator, eventStore})
    Bridge->>MCPServer: buildMcpServer(client)
    Bridge->>MCPServer: server.connect(transport)
    Transport->>Sessions: onsessioninitialized callback<br/>sessions.set(sessionId, {...})
    Transport-->>Client: 200 OK + Mcp-Session-Id header<br/>SSE stream with initialize response
    
    Note over Client,MCPServer: Tool Calls
    Client->>Bridge: POST /mcp<br/>Mcp-Session-Id: abc-123
    Bridge->>Sessions: sessions.get(sessionId)
    Sessions-->>Bridge: {transport, server, eventStore}
    Bridge->>Transport: handleRequest(req, res, body)
    Transport->>MCPServer: CallToolRequestSchema handler
    MCPServer->>MCPServer: Execute tool logic
    MCPServer-->>Transport: JSON-RPC response
    Transport->>EventStore: storeEvent(sessionId, message)
    Transport-->>Client: SSE event with result
    
    Note over Client,MCPServer: Resumption (Last-Event-ID)
    Client->>Bridge: GET /mcp<br/>Mcp-Session-Id: abc-123<br/>Last-Event-ID: abc-123-17...
    Bridge->>EventStore: replayEventsAfter(sessionId, lastEventId)
    EventStore-->>Bridge: [missed events]
    Bridge-->>Client: SSE stream with replayed events
    
    Note over Client,MCPServer: Session Cleanup
    Bridge->>Bridge: sessionSweep interval (5 min)<br/>TTL check: 1 hour idle
    Bridge->>Sessions: sessions.delete(sessionId)
    Bridge->>EventStore: removeStream(sessionId)<br/>stopCleanup()